# MkDocs Material Theme

Reference: `~/Developer/reference/mkdocs/docs.txt` (scraped Material docs).

## Configuration hierarchy

1. **`mkdocs.yml`** — behavior (nav features, palette, fonts, plugins)
2. **`docs/stylesheets/tokens.css`** — CSS variables (`--md-*`, `--cs-*`)
3. **`docs/stylesheets/nav.css`** — sidebar-only overrides (keep minimal)
4. **`docs/stylesheets/extra.css`** — imports the above; do not add rules here

Prefer theme features over CSS. Extend via `theme.custom_dir: overrides` only when HTML structure must change.

## Navigation structure

Three header tabs keep the site clean: **Home · Lessons · Practice**.
Inside the **Lessons** tab the sidebar shows module sections (Foundations, Routing, etc.) with collapsible per-lesson groups.

```yaml
nav:
  - Home: index.md
  - Lessons:
      - Foundations:
          - Lesson 1:
              - Guide: lesson-01/introduction.md
              - Plain-language: lesson-01/plain-language.md
              - Quick study: lesson-01/quick-study-guide.md
              - Quiz: lesson-01/quiz.md
  - Practice: practice-questions.md
```

Lesson labels are short (`Lesson N`) — topic description lives in the Guide page title only.
Child labels are always: **Guide**, **Plain-language**, **Quick study**, **Quiz**.

### Feature flags (current)

| Feature | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `navigation.tabs` + `navigation.tabs.sticky` | Module groups in header tabs |
| `navigation.path` | Breadcrumbs above page title |
| `navigation.instant` + `navigation.instant.prefetch` | SPA-like page loads |
| `navigation.tracking` | URL updates with TOC anchor |
| `toc.follow` | TOC scrolls to active heading |

### Do NOT enable

| Feature | Why |
|---------|-----|
| `navigation.sections` | Top-level sections always expanded; fights collapsible lessons |
| `navigation.expand` | Expands every subsection by default |
| `navigation.prune` | Replaces collapsible sections with flat links (large-site optimization) |
| `navigation.indexes` | Duplicates section title as first child; use explicit `Guide:` label instead |

## Colors and fonts

- Palette in `mkdocs.yml` (`primary`, `accent`, light/dark `scheme`)
- Custom brand colors: set `primary: custom` then override `--md-primary-fg-color*` in `tokens.css`
- Fonts: `theme.font.text` / `theme.font.code` in `mkdocs.yml` (Google Fonts)

## When editing nav

Update **both** `mkdocs.yml` nav and `docs/index.md` modules table (see `project-context.mdc`).

## Plugins (approved)

| Plugin | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `privacy` | Self-host Google Fonts and external JS (MathJax) |
| `search` | Built-in client-side search |
| `tags` | Topic index via front matter `tags:` |
| `social` | Open Graph preview cards (requires `mkdocs-material[imaging]`) |
| `optimize` | Compress images at build time (CI only — `enabled: !ENV [CI, false]`; needs `pngquant`) |
| `glightbox` | Image lightbox |
| `git-revision-date-localized` | Last-updated dates |
| `git-authors` | Git author metadata |
| `mkdocs_quiz` | Interactive quizzes |

Do **not** add `navigation.prune`, `offline`, or Google Analytics.

**Math (LaTeX):** `pymdownx.arithmatex` + `docs/javascripts/mathjax.js` (config, load first) + MathJax 3 in `extra_javascript`. Author with `$...$` inline and `$$...$$` display.

## Feedback widget

GitHub Issues integration via [`docs/javascripts/feedback.js`](docs/javascripts/feedback.js):

- `extra.analytics.feedback` in `mkdocs.yml` renders the widget
- Positive rating shows a thank-you note
- Negative rating opens a pre-filled GitHub issue (`data: 0` in feedback.js)
- Hide per page: `hide: [feedback]` in front matter

## Front matter conventions

**Tags** (small vocabulary):

```yaml
tags:
  - lesson-04
  - bgp
  - quick-study
```

Use `lesson-NN`, topic (`tcp`, `bgp`, `sdn`, `security`, …), and format (`plain-language`, `quick-study`, `quiz`) where applicable.

**Search boost** (study formats rank higher):

```yaml
search:
  boost: 2    # plain-language and quick-study
  boost: 1.5  # quiz
```

**Exclude from search:** `search: { exclude: true }` on `docs/lectures/` if linked into build.

## Schema validation

VS Code autocomplete: [`.vscode/settings.json`](.vscode/settings.json) maps `mkdocs.yml` to the Material schema.
